fields.description:
Geoink mapping  ProgramTest Index and StageDie TestResultsJson

Update the WAFER_INSERTION_STAGE_DIE TEST_RESULTS_JSON

If testValue is not passed in the GeoInk input request the default value taken is 1L set this testValue either in the existing JSON at the end index  or for the new JSON set at the index from this method argument.

 

The Index value passed as argument to be used only for new StageDie (testResultsJson==null).  Update the PROGRAM_TEST results_index for existing or new failedTests.

Index value is the total size of the ProgramTest associated with the Program to be used only for new StageDie (testResultsJson==null) waferInsertionStage.getProgram().getTests().size()

Only for new StageDie that is testResultsJson==null add null at prior index of setting this floating testValue. example index is 4 set null,null,null,null,testValue

Set null at all previous indexes prior to index from this method argument
fields.summary: Geoink mapping  ProgramTest Index and StageDie TestResultsJson

fields.description:
STDF Recovery on Tokyo server.

Currently STDF Recovery is not configured to work on any Tokyo servers. It is configured to work only on the Frankfurt Servers.

Reason – The parser is deployed on the Frankfurt server and puts the processed files on NFS location - /oef_stdf_processor_prd/processed/

              For Tokyo, the file location is different /opt_stdf_processor_prd/processed/

So, the files in the Frankfurt Processed directory is not visible to the Tokyo Server.

             

If the service is required on Tokyo server as well, we need to design and implement, but Network latency might incur additional delays in the recovery as compared to the Frankfurt server.

 

Two changes I see in implementation-
 # We need to mount OCIFS /{+}localdisk{+}/{+}ocradmin{+}/CloudStorage/{+}renesasglobal{+}/oef_stdf_archive_prod on Tokyo server as well, but Network latency might incur additional delays in the recovery.
 # There will be configuration change in the gym_service to handle /oef_stdf_processor_prd/processed/  for Frankfurt server and /opt_stdf_processor_prd/processed/ for Tokyo server or handling in the code based on server we either check or ignore the NFS processed directory.

 

We need to move files into OCI quickly so that they could be found on OCI from Tokyo server.

As suggested by Sriram currently we run the automated upload job using OCIFS only on weekends so 5 days data will be the NFS processed directory that could not be recovered from Tokyo server as they are not visible.

But with future implementation of Rclone and daily automated upload job this timeline could be further reduced.
fields.summary: STDF Recovery on Tokyo server - Production
